# DBAI: AI-Orchestrated Production Defect Response
### Pitch for IT & Engineering Leadership

---

## Elevator Pitch (30 seconds)

> Every production defect costs your team 4–8 hours of overhead that has nothing to do with fixing the bug — triage, ticket creation, context-gathering, manual handoffs between ServiceNow and Jira, coordinating deployments, and remembering to close the Problem record.
>
> DBAI eliminates that overhead. A ServiceNow Problem fires a webhook. The system triages it with AI, creates a properly scoped Jira Defect, notifies the right developer with full context already loaded, assists the fix, runs the tests, deploys on approval, and closes the SNow Problem automatically.
>
> **Your engineers fix bugs. The system handles everything else.**

---

## Slide 1 — The Problem You're Solving Every Day

Every production defect triggers the same manual chain:

1. Alert fires → someone notices → SNow Problem created (maybe)
2. Lead triages it → context gathered manually from logs, tickets, Slack
3. Jira Defect created → manually, inconsistently, sometimes skipped
4. Developer picks it up → spends 20–40 minutes piecing together context
5. Fix built → manually tested → manually coordinated for deploy
6. SNow Problem closed → remembered eventually, or left open

**The bug itself takes 2 hours. The process around it takes 6.**

